AntVoice Privacy Policy

    1. Home

     Privacy Policy

About AntVoice Services

   AntVoice specializes in creating personalized recommendations and
   advertisements. We work with online partners to build a personnalized
   experience and advertisements for users who visit their website or
   mobile applications and with publishers to display personalized
   advertisements. Our aim is to deliver recommendations or advertisements
   by displaying products and/or personalized banners that you might be
   interested in, based on your recent browsing behavior. For example, if
   you visit and browse on Website/mobile application A, you will get
   personalized recommendation during your browsing session based on the
   products or contents of your browsing session. Morover, on a subsequent
   online visit to Website/mobile application B, you may see ads
   personalized by your browsing history on Website/mobile application A.
   With our service, you should receive personalized recommendations and
   ads that are more relevant for you than the standard advertising you
   would receive without AntVoice.

Our Technology

   We collect information via technical cookies placed on your browser.
   Thanks to this technology, AntVoice “tags” visitors to its partners’
   websites and mobile applications. Users tagged by AntVoice are given a
   technical identifier. At no point does AntVoice collect identifying
   personal data such as your name or address. AntVoice only analyses the
   products or content viewed by the visitor. Our partners’ advertisements
   are displayed on many websites, also known as “publishers.” These
   publishers may also place cookies on your browser. These cookies are
   there so that the publishers recognize that AntVoice has a personalized
   advertisement available for your browser. Their use are governed by the
   specific privacy policies of the publishers which can be accessed
   directly from their websites. We may also receive ID-syncing
   information from trusted partners using diverse linking methods for the
   same purpose and with the same level of guarantees in terms of Privacy
   and Data Protection. We may also store anonymous identifiers inside
   your browser “local storage” when our technology is used as a
   recommendation engine provided to media and retailing websites. See
   “data collection and use” paragraph to learn more.

Data collection and usage

   We do not know who you are. We only collect and use technical data
   relating to your browsing navigation to display personalized
   advertisements. To serve relevant ads and recommendations, we have to
   be able to single out patterns but we never willingly store data that
   would allow identification of a person (such as name, surname, phone
   number, address, etc.). We collect data related to your browsing
   activity through cookies, local storages or advertising IDs that
   record:
     * events related to your activity on our partner’s website (such as
       the number of pages viewed, the products or contents you viewed on
       that website, your searches made on the partner’s website)
     * events related to the AntVoice activity such as the number of
       recommendations or ads displayed to you.
     * information related to your device (device type, operating system,
       version)
     * non-precise information related to your geography and derived from
       the truncated IP address of your connection. We do not use or store
       full IP address for targeting purposes.

   These data will be collected to generate Interest-Based Recommendations
   or advertising. We also collect technical user identifiers from our
   partners for the purpose of linking the different browsers and mobile
   apps you use and serve you relevant recommendations and ads based on
   your behaviour across environments (“ID syncing”). For that purpose we
   process and store
     * Technical IDs of our partners, or a hashed version of your email
       address ensuring the non-reversibility of your information.
     * Mobile advertising IDs (such as Apple IDFA or Google AAID) which
       are specific technical data created by mobile manufacturers to
       allow personalization and customer analytics in a secure and
       non-identifying way for users

   If you do not want to receive ads displayed by AntVoice on your current
   browser and browsers, you can disable the display of AntVoice ads
   clicking on the button bellow :
   Opt-out from AntVoice’s systemYou are now unsubscribed from AntVoice’s
   system

   Opting-out from AntVoice services will trigger the deletion of your
   linking information and will prevent the future linking of the
   opted-out browser using a new cookie on your browser. We have to
   maintain this cookie on your browser in order to recognize you as
   having opted out from our service. You must opt out again if you clear
   that cookie from a browser, use another browser, or use a new device to
   access the internet. You can also opt out of AntVoice’s service
   directly from the privacy statements of our partners. Please note that
   if you are using an ad-blocker you may have to pause blocking or
   whitelist our website to be able to opt out effectively.

   Web browser environment and in-app environment are separate. If you do
   not want to receive AntVoice on mobile app environments, please refer
   to your operating system settings, or follow instructions below:
     * Android Users, follow the instructions provided by Google Support
     * iOS users, follow the instructions provided by Apple Support Center

   Please note that this is a device setting and will disable
   interest-based ads from all providers, and not just for AntVoice

We do not collect any identifying information

   We do not know who you are. We do not know your address, your place of
   work, your date of birth, your email address, your phone number. We do
   not use or store full IP address. We do not collect hardware-based
   identifiers such as UDID, Mac Address and do not use fingerprinting
   methods. We do not collect sensitive information (such as religion,
   political opinion, health…). We do not create segments to specifically
   target children. We do not process any information which could be used
   by AntVoice or any of its partners, directly or indirectly, to
   determine the personal identity of users.

We may share aggregated data

   We may share non identifying data such as aggregated data and technical
   identifiers with our partners, i.e. data that does not permit you to be
   directly identified. We only share aggregated data upon approval of our
   partners and in compliance with our commercial agreements. We partner
   with Ad exchanges platforms to buy ad placements through auctions.
   Before the auction we link our ID with the ad exchange platform and
   then participate to the auction by sending the bid price and the banner
   code to display.

Data security and retention

   We retain the technical data that we collect for up to 13 months from
   the date of collection. Our cookies expire 13 months after they are
   last updated.

   Please note that we may update or change this privacy policy. If we
   revise our privacy policy, we will post those changes to this privacy
   statement, and to other places we deem appropriate, so that you are
   aware of what information we collect, how we use it, and under what
   circumstances, if any we disclose it. If we make any material changes
   we will notify you by means of a notice on this site prior to the
   change becoming effective.

   Last updated: April 17, 2018

